SIMPLE: shelfy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shelfy
<hw>Shelf"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding
in shelves; full of dangerous shallows.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>shelfy</xex>
coast.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of strata of rock.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The tillable fields are in some places . . . so <qex>shelfy</qex>
that the corn hath much ado to fasten its root.</q>
<rj><qau>Carew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shell</ent>⟦br⟧
